==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mandibular
<hw>Man*dib"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>mandibulaire</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a mandible;
like a mandible.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The principal
mandibular bone; the mandible.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mandibular arch</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>the
most anterior visceral arch, -- that in which the mandible is
developed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mandibular joint</ent>⟦br⟧
